The paper deals with Bayesian games, which are a subfield of game theory, and discusses the Price of Anarchy, which is a measure of inefficiency in game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of smoothness in analyzing these games, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and machine learning, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the efficiency of different auction mechanisms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
